### Rewriting the radical as a rational power

$\begin{align}
f(x)&=\sqrt{x}
\\\\
&=x^{^{\Large\frac{1}{2}}}
\end{align}$

### Differentiating using the power rule

$\begin{align}
&\phantom{=}f'(x)
\\\\
&=\dfrac{d}{dx}\left(x^{^{\Large\frac{1}{2}}}\right)
\\\\
&=\dfrac{1}{2}x^{^{\Large\frac{1}{2}-1}}\qquad\gray{\text{The power rule}}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{1}{2}x^{^{\Large-\frac{1}{2}}}
\end{align}$

